			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				for a realy efficient website on all forms of tailoring, visit <BR>
<BR>
Http://www.enteract.com/~lokari/everquest/tailoring.html<BR>
<BR>
this displays all info on how to make PW, Studded, reinforced, raw, cured and shadow silk, wu's fighting gauntlets, tailor-made whip, backpacks, etc.  and the ingredients on the different armors as well as a chart of AC and WT of the armors and when the tailoring types become trivial (won't gain you any more levels on tailoring skill).  this site tells you everything you need to know about tailoring exceplt for how to bring it up.  obivously, the basic way is to use practise points from every EXP level your character gains.  for basic people who are using those points on more important things like 1h slashing / blunt, you can kill large and giant spiders and make silk swatches out of pairs of spider silks, not spiderling silks, in small sewing kits. making silk swatches is fail-proof, so you'll make one every time, and they sell for exactly the same as what you made them out of(2 silks).  or you can do it the other old-fashioned way by trying to make patchwork out of ruined pelts and patterns. I suggest using the spider silk technique as it is cheap and effective, but you won't loot silks out of EVERY spider. i've tried spiders in West Karana and Verant seems to have deprived all of them of their silk. other zones, especially the desert tarantulas of North Ro, might give you better luck if you're a lvl 10+ character.  one last note, making the swatches won't boost up your skill level EVERY time you make one. it's the same as every skill: every few times you use it you'll gain a lvl in it<BR>
<BR>
hope this works for y'all. if you need more assistance, and you're in the Tunare Server, look for Fithos or Malacandra of the Mercenaries guild. Good luck to thee. =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
