	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This giude really needs to cover the silk sewing stuff. But since it isn't, here is a guide on Raw silk items:<BR>
<BR>
HOW TO MAKE SWATCHES<BR>
To make swatches, you will need the following: Two spider silks (Which are found on large spiders), a Large sewing kit, and at least lvl 15 in sewing. Now, put the two spider silks into the large sewing kit and click on the combine button and voila! A Silk Swatch!<BR>
<BR>
MAKING RAW SILK ITEMS:<BR>
To make raw silk items, you will need the following: a pattern and a swatch. Now, all you got to do is put the two items into a large sewing kit and with a high enough skill lvl (Not to sure what it is) and combine the two. Now you have a raw silk whatever.<BR>
<BR>
Advanced silk is a little more expensive, but I will post how to make it later.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
