				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(6,161114);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >6</font></a></b>
				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(7,161114);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >7</font></a></b>
				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(8,161114);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >8</font></a></b>
				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(9,161114);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >9</font></a></b>
				<b><a href="javascript:openWindow(10,161114);"><font face="Verdana" size="1" >10</font></a></b>
				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK for Raw silk you need 2 spider silks, not SPIDERLING silks combine them in a sewing kit. Now you have a silk swatch. Do this and Patchwork until you get to about 26 when Patch work no longer gives you points. Then with all those swatches you have around now you can go to a tailoring store and pick up some patterns. Dont buy tunic or legging patterns yet, those are a lttle harder to make. With all these patterns now you need 1 silk and 1 pattern. Combine them in your kit and you might succed you might fail. Doesn't matter keep doing it until your skill is 30 or you have a complete set minus the legs and the tunic. Now for the tunic and legs you you need 2 swatches and 1 pattern. The swatches have to be in different slots so you will need a large sewing kit at this point. They cost about 1 plat. Keep trying with the tunic and leggings until you have both. Then go back to making one of the other things that only require 1 swatch until raw silk is trivial at about 35 i think. To proceed with tailoring you will have to either start brewing or buy Heady Kiolas. To start brewing you will need snake scales(hunting in the newbie zones just outside citues works best for these) water(make sure it is store bought not summoned) and a bottle.(these are dark purple and look like theres something im them already.) Now with these you need to find a cask in a store. Ir's really big with a coil coming out of it. (not the casks you buy from mrchants.) Put 1 of each of these things in and then combine. If you fail you will get the bottle back. Do this until brewing is 21 and the bog juice that you made is trivial. Now for the Heady Kiolas. you need water and a bottle still but you also need 2 bags of Kiola sap and you don't need snake scales anymore. Put 1 water and 1 bottle in the brewing cask and 2 bags of Kiola sap, in different slots. Hit combine and repeat. Once you get to 30 you can make Heady Kiolas fairly reguraly(sp). For cured silk masks you need to put 1 heady kiola in our tailoring Kit along with 1 mask pattern and 1 swatch. I can't remember the formulas for the rest of the armour yet but you can find that out on your own.<BR>
<BR>
As for HQ bear skins and cat pelts...<BR>
<BR>
The bear skins are used for making 10 slot backpacks. The cat pelts are used for quivers and whips. You should have a skill of 75 before you can make these often. You can start trying at 50 though. the same skill lvls apply for Wus fighting gauntlets.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
